Bright and inviting 2-roomapartment of approx. 55 sqm with a lovely green-facing balcony, located in the popular Landlust area in Bos en Lommer. The beautiful Erasmuspark is just a short walk away.

Curious to see more? Step inside!

Location:
Willem Leevendstraat is situated in the heart of Bos en Lommer, a vibrant and green neighbourhood in Amsterdam-West that has become one of the city's most sought-after residential areas. It combines the energy of city life with a relaxed atmosphere, featuring tree-lined streets, wide pavements and charming squares. Within walking distance, you'll find a variety of local shops, supermarkets and cosy cafés along Bos en Lommerweg and the renovated Bos en Lommerplein. Whether you're looking for your daily groceries, a great cup of coffee or dinner at one of the area's trendy restaurants, everything is close at hand.

For those who enjoy outdoor living, both Erasmuspark and Westerpark are nearby, offering plenty of opportunities for walking, exercising or simply relaxing in the green surroundings. Accessibility is excellent as well. By bike, you can reach the Jordaan or Amsterdam city centre in around ten minutes, while tram, bus and metro connections provide quick access to Amsterdam Central Station and Sloterdijk Station. The A10 ring road is only a few minutes away by car, making it easy to leave the city.

Layout:
The apartment is located on the first floor. Upon entering, the central hallway provides access to all rooms.
The bright and inviting living room immediately creates a spacious feeling thanks to its open layout. 

The living and dining areas flow seamlessly into one another, creating an attractive living space with ample room for both a comfortable seating area and a generous dining table. At the front of the apartment, the dining area benefits from large windows that allow an abundance of natural light to flood the space while offering pleasant views of the street. Adjacent to the dining area is the open-plan kitchen, which has been thoughtfully designed and fitted with built-in appliances. Its position at the front of the apartment creates a sociable connection with the living area.

At the rear of the property, you'll find the spacious bedroom. Quietly positioned, it easily accommodates a double bed, wardrobe space and even a home office corner if desired. French doors provide direct access to the balcony.

The balcony extends across the full width of the apartment and overlooks lush greenery, offering a peaceful outdoor space to enjoy your morning coffee or unwind after a busy day.

The bathroom is neatly finished and features a bathtub with shower, a washbasin with vanity unit and a heated towel rail. A separate toilet is accessible from the hallway.

Overall, the layout is both practical and comfortable, with a bright living area at the front, a peaceful bedroom at the rear and a generous balcony that serves as a natural extension of the living space.

Homeowners' Association (VvE):
The Homeowners' Association (VvE) of Willem Leevendstraat 5 is self-managed by the owners of the upper-floor apartments. The owners are actively involved in the management of the building, take responsibility for its maintenance and ensure that all VvE matters are carefully administered. The association has an up-to-date Long-Term Maintenance Plan (MJOP), which is consistently followed. The monthly service charge amounts to €75.

Ground Lease:
The apartment is situated on municipal leasehold land (erfpacht). The current lease period runs until 2049. An annual ground rent (canon) of €289.27 is payable and is indexed annually.

The current owner has already opted into the perpetual leasehold system under the favourable 2016 General Provisions. From 31 July 2049, the annual ground rent will be €302.78, plus annual inflation/indexation.

Details: 
